 897:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c **** /**
 898:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   * @brief  Clears the USARTx's pending flags.
 899:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   * @param  USARTx: Select the USART or the UART peripheral. 
 900:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *   This parameter can be one of the following values:
 901:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *   USART1, USART2, USART3, UART4 or UART5.
 902:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   * @param  USART_FLAG: specifies the flag to clear.
 903:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *   This parameter can be any combination of the following values:
 904:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     @arg USART_FLAG_CTS:  CTS Change flag (not available for UART4 and UART5).
 905:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     @arg USART_FLAG_LBD:  LIN Break detection flag.
 906:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     @arg USART_FLAG_TC:   Transmission Complete flag.
 907:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     @arg USART_FLAG_RXNE: Receive data register not empty flag.
 908:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *   
 909:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   * @note
 910:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *   - PE (Parity error), FE (Framing error), NE (Noise error), ORE (OverRun 
 911:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     error) and IDLE (Idle line detected) flags are cleared by software 
 912:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     sequence: a read operation to USART_SR register (USART_GetFlagStatus()) 
 913:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     followed by a read operation to USART_DR register (USART_ReceiveData()).
 914:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *   - RXNE flag can be also cleared by a read to the USART_DR register 
 915:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     (USART_ReceiveData()).
 916:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *   - TC flag can be also cleared by software sequence: a read operation to 
 917:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     USART_SR register (USART_GetFlagStatus()) followed by a write operation
 918:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     to USART_DR register (USART_SendData()).
 919:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *   - TXE flag is cleared only by a write to the USART_DR register 
 920:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   *     (USART_SendData()).
 921:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   * @retval None
 922:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c ****   */
 923:../Libraries//STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_usart.c **** void USART_ClearFlag(USART_TypeDef* USARTx, uint16_t USART_FLAG)
